<h2 style="color: #0F19A0 !important;font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;margin: 15px 0;font-weight: 700;font-size: 18px;line-height: 1.111111111;padding: 15px 0;">
  How to prepare for your appointment
</h2>

<% if @appointment.pension_wise? %>
  <%= p do %>
    You’ll usually benefit more from a Pension Wise appointment if you:
  <% end %>

  <ol style="color: #0B0C0C;font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;margin-top: 15px;margin-bottom: 15px;font-size: 16px;line-height: 1.315789474;">
    <li>
      Ask each pension provider:
      <ul style="color: #0B0C0C;font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;margin-top: 15px;margin-bottom: 15px;font-size: 16px;line-height: 1.315789474;">
        <li>how much your pension is currently worth</li>
        <li>if your pension has any special features, like a guaranteed pot value or annuity rate.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      Check your State Pension forecast:
      <ul style="color: #0B0C0C;font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;margin-top: 15px;margin-bottom: 15px;font-size: 16px;line-height: 1.315789474;">
        <li>online at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/">GOV.UK</a></li>
        <li>by calling 0800 731 0175 between 8am and 6pm, Monday to Friday.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      Have details of your other finances, like:
      <ul style="color: #0B0C0C;font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;margin-top: 15px;margin-bottom: 15px;font-size: 16px;line-height: 1.315789474;">
        <li>savings and investments</li>
        <li>debts and repayments.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      Think about your plan for retirement, such as:
      <ul style="color: #0B0C0C;font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;margin-top: 15px;margin-bottom: 15px;font-size: 16px;line-height: 1.315789474;">
        <li>when you’d like to stop working</li>
        <li>what type of pension income you’d like.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <%= p do %>
    For more information, see <a href="https://www.moneyhelper.org.uk/en/pensions-and-retirement/pension-wise/preparing-for-your-appointment">How to prepare for your Pension Wise appointment</a>.
  <% end %>
<% else %>
  <%= p do %>
    During the appointment, we'll ask about the pension transfer you're making and your financial situation.
  <% end %>

  <%= p do %>
    To help us give you relevant guidance, it’s useful if you can find out:
  <% end %>

  <ol style="color: #0B0C0C;font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;margin-top: 15px;margin-bottom: 15px;font-size: 16px;line-height: 1.315789474;">
    <li>The type of pension you already have – usually defined contribution or defined benefit – and the name of the product, like a personal or workplace pension.</li>
    <li>The type and name of the pension scheme you want to transfer to.</li>
    <li>The fees and charges for both schemes.</li>
    <li>If you’re transferring a defined contribution pension, how each scheme plans to invest your money – including the funds or types of asset they use. You can ask each pension provider if you’re not sure.</li>
    <li>Why your current pension provider has asked you to book this appointment – they might refer to their concerns about your transfer as a red or amber flag.</li>
    <li>Details of any financial adviser you’ve used.</li>
  </ol>

  <%= p do %>
    It’s also helpful to:
  <% end %>

  <ul style="color: #0B0C0C;font-family: Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;margin-top: 15px;margin-bottom: 15px;font-size: 16px;line-height: 1.315789474;">
    <li>have information about all the retirement income you might have, including other pensions</li>
    <li>think about your plans for retirement, including when you want to start taking your pension.</li>
  </ul>
<% end %>
